results.name: Smallest prime which occurs in prime power factorization of A240751(n)! with exponent n.
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: A240751(4)=6, since 6!=2^4*3^2*5. Here, only the prime 2 is in power 4, thus A240755(4)=2.
